#intro
https://git.sr.ht/~martanne/dvtm
dvtm not implementing session management.
to use session management use abduco

##tutorial
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-dvtm-and-dtach-as-a-terminal-window-manager-on-an-ubuntu-vps

##problem
カーソルの形状が､insertだろうが､viewだろうがかわらない｡(shell,vimともに)
    dvtm側での処理が必要なのだが､対応している様子はない｡
ターミナル側､vim側では､信号を送っているが､dvtmで適切に処理されていない｡
tmuxだと設定することで見られるようだ｡
    ex) https://blog.terriblelabs.com/blog/2013/02/09/stupid-vim-tricks-how-to-change-insert-mode-cursor-shape-with-tmux/
tmuxはtmuxでstのwindow swallowができない｡
###solution
https://github.com/martanne/dvtm/pull/129/commits/130355a31b8919903eec16636a32995f70ac5c3e
https://github.com/martanne/dvtm/pull/129

#specific terminal 
$ DVTM_TERM=rxvt dvtm

#default MOD
CTRL+g

#change MOD at runtime | CTRL+ g to CTRL + b
dvtm -m ^b

#Window
MOD+c   #new window
MOD+x(+x)   #close window
MOD+j,k | MOD+[1..9]    #switch amoung the windows
MOD+.   #minimize
MOD+a   #input to all visible window toggle


#Layout
MOD+h,l #shrink,enlarge master area
MOD+enter   #zoom window into the master area
MOD+i,d #increase,decrease the number of windows in the master area
MOD+space   #cycle through 4 types of layouts
MOD+m   #fullscreen

futher layouts are disabled by default


#Tagging
MOD-0 view all windows with any tag
Mod-v-Tab toggles to the previously selected tags
MOD-v-[1..n] view all windows with nth tag
Mod-V-[1..n] add/remove all windows with nth tag to/from the view
Mod-t-[1..n] apply nth tag to focused window
Mod-T-[1..n] add/remove nth tag to/from focused window


#statusbar
script


#Copymode
MOD+e   #pipes the whole scroll buffer content to an external editor. What ever the editor writes to stdout is remembered by dvtm
MOD+p   #paste

some setup are needed

#Mouse
MOD+M   #disable
    dvtm -M
    modify config.def.h
Shift+LMB   #select
Shift+RMB   #copy
Shift+MMB   #paste

#mouse scroll?
